Overview: Tidy data is a merged dataset that is derived from a database that includes 8 separate datasets. 

Source data: https://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/getdata%2Fprojectfiles%2FUCI%20HAR%20Dataset.zip

Let's break down the 8 source datasets (additional details can be found at the data source website: http://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Human+Activity+Recognition+Using+Smartphones):

1. 'features.txt': List names of the feature variables

2. 'activity_labels.txt': Provides a class label to each activity name

3. 'X_train.txt': Training set for the features variables

4. 'y_train.txt': Training labels for the activity names

5. 'X_test.txt': Test set for the features variables

6. 'y_test.txt': Test labels for the activity names

7. 'subject_train.txt': observations are for subjects who performed the activities

8. 'subject_test.txt': observations are for subjects who performed the activities

Additional details on the variables can be found here: https://www.elen.ucl.ac.be/Proceedings/esann/esannpdf/es2013-84.pdf

